# CesiumJS Geospatial Application

A sophisticated CesiumJS web application for advanced geospatial exploration, featuring comprehensive map visualization and interaction capabilities with professional WebGL rendering.

## Features

- CesiumJS with advanced projection support
- Dynamic layer management and interactive map controls
- Responsive design with high-fidelity geospatial rendering
- Enhanced UI with subtle animations and transparent interface elements
- Interactive WMS and feature layer integration
- Flat Earth mode with EPSG:4326 projection support

## Deployment

This application is configured for deployment on Replit and other cloud platforms using a Python-based static file server.

### Local Development

```bash
python main.py
```

The application will be available at `http://localhost:5000`

### Environment Variables

- `PORT` - Server port (default: 5000)

## Architecture

- **Frontend**: Pure HTML/CSS/JavaScript with CesiumJS
- **Backend**: Python HTTP server with CORS support
- **Dependencies**: No external dependencies (uses Python standard library)
- **Data Sources**: OpenStreetMap and other open geospatial data providers

## Technical Notes

- No external dependencies required (uses Python standard library)
- CesiumJS assets loaded from official CDN
- All geospatial data from open sources (no API keys needed)
- Optimized for static file serving with proper MIME types
- Ready for production deployment with security headers
